<li><span class="reference"><svg class="octicon octicon-git-merge merged color-fg-done mr-1" title="Merged" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5.45 5.154A4.25 4.25 0 0 0 9.25 7.5h1.378a2.251 2.251 0 1 1 0 1.5H9.25A5.734 5.734 0 0 1 5 7.123v3.505a2.25 2.25 0 1 1-1.5 0V5.372a2.25 2.25 0 1 1 1.95-.218ZM4.25 13.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5Zm8.5-4.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5ZM5 3.25a.75.75 0 1 0 0 .005V3.25Z"></path></svg><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="776662862" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/80534" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/80534/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/80534">Use #[doc = include_str!()] in std<span class="issue-shorthand"> #80534</span></a></span></li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto">Implementation history</h2>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Initial proposal: <span class="reference"><svg class="octicon octicon-issue-closed closed mr-1" title="Closed" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M11.28 6.78a.75.75 0 0 0-1.06-1.06L7.25 8.69 5.78 7.22a.75.75 0 0 0-1.06 1.06l2 2a.75.75 0 0 0 1.06 0l3.5-3.5Z"></path><path d="M16 8A8 8 0 1 1 0 8a8 8 0 0 1 16 0Zm-1.5 0a6.5 6.5 0 1 0-13 0 6.5 6.5 0 0 0 13 0Z"></path></svg><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="374642448" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/55414" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/issues/55414/hovercard?comment_id=554005412&amp;comment_type=issue_comment" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/55414#issuecomment-554005412">ICE in macro: doc meta with expr on an item, string concat, stringify!(...)<span class="issue-shorthand"> #55414 (comment)</span></a></span></li>
<li>Experiment to see how much code it would break: <span class="reference"><svg class="octicon octicon-git-pull-request-closed closed color-fg-closed mr-1" title="Closed" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3.25 1A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 4 5.372v5.256a2.251 2.251 0 1 1-1.5 0V5.372A2.251 2.251 0 0 1 3.25 1Zm9.5 5.5a.75.75 0 0 1 .75.75v3.378a2.251 2.251 0 1 1-1.5 0V7.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75Zm-2.03-5.273a.75.75 0 0 1 1.06 0l.97.97.97-.97a.748.748 0 0 1 1.265.332.75.75 0 0 1-.205.729l-.97.97.97.97a.751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018l-.97-.97-.97.97a.749.749 0 0 1-1.275-.326.749.749 0 0 1 .215-.734l.97-.97-.97-.97a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.06ZM2.5 3.25a.75.75 0 1 0 1.5 0 .75.75 0 0 0-1.5 0ZM3.25 12a.75.75 0 1 0 0 1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0-1.5Zm9.5 0a.75.75 0 1 0 0 1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0-1.5Z"></path></svg><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="534413987" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/67121" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/67121/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/67121">[experiment] Expand macros in inert key-value attributes<span class="issue-shorthand"> #67121</span></a></span></li>
<li>Preliminary work to restrict expansion that would conflict with this<br>
feature: <span class="reference"><svg class="octicon octicon-git-merge merged color-fg-done mr-1" title="Merged" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5.45 5.154A4.25 4.25 0 0 0 9.25 7.5h1.378a2.251 2.251 0 1 1 0 1.5H9.25A5.734 5.734 0 0 1 5 7.123v3.505a2.25 2.25 0 1 1-1.5 0V5.372a2.25 2.25 0 1 1 1.95-.218ZM4.25 13.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5Zm8.5-4.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5ZM5 3.25a.75.75 0 1 0 0 .005V3.25Z"></path></svg><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="709771746" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/77271" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/77271/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/77271">Expand <code>NtExpr</code> tokens only in key-value attributes<span class="issue-shorthand"> #77271</span></a></span></li>
<li>Initial implementation: <span class="reference"><svg class="octicon octicon-git-merge merged color-fg-done mr-1" title="Merged" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5.45 5.154A4.25 4.25 0 0 0 9.25 7.5h1.378a2.251 2.251 0 1 1 0 1.5H9.25A5.734 5.734 0 0 1 5 7.123v3.505a2.25 2.25 0 1 1-1.5 0V5.372a2.25 2.25 0 1 1 1.95-.218ZM4.25 13.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5Zm8.5-4.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5ZM5 3.25a.75.75 0 1 0 0 .005V3.25Z"></path></svg><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="738277339" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/78837" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/78837/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/78837">Accept arbitrary expressions in key-value attributes at parse time<span class="issue-shorthand"> #78837</span></a></span></li>
<li>Fix for an ICE: <span class="reference"><svg class="octicon octicon-git-merge merged color-fg-done mr-1" title="Merged" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5.45 5.154A4.25 4.25 0 0 0 9.25 7.5h1.378a2.251 2.251 0 1 1 0 1.5H9.25A5.734 5.734 0 0 1 5 7.123v3.505a2.25 2.25 0 1 1-1.5 0V5.372a2.25 2.25 0 1 1 1.95-.218ZM4.25 13.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5Zm8.5-4.5a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5ZM5 3.25a.75.75 0 1 0 0 .005V3.25Z"></path></svg><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="777083709" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/80563" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/80563/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/80563">resolve/expand: Improve attribute expansion on macro definitions and calls<span class="issue-shorthand"> #80563</span></a></span></li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto">Unresolved Questions</h2>
<p dir="auto"><del><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="837337020" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/83366" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/83366/hovercard?comment_id=805180738&amp;comment_type=issue_comment" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/83366#issuecomment-805180738">#83366 (comment)</a> listed some concerns, but they have been resolved as of this final report.</del></p>
<a id="user-content-additional-information">
<h2 dir="auto">Additional Information</h2>
</a>
<p dir="auto">There are two workarounds that have a similar effect for <code class="notranslate">#[doc]</code><br>
attributes on nightly. One is to emulate this behavior by using a limited version of this feature that was stabilized for historical reasons:</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-rust notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="macro_rules! forward_inner_docs {
    ($e:expr =&gt; $i:item) =&gt; {
        #[doc = $e]
        $i
    };
}

forward_inner_docs!(include_str!(&quot;lib.rs&quot;) =&gt; struct S {});"><pre class="notranslate"><span class="pl-k">macro_rules!</span> forward_inner_docs <span class="pl-kos">{</span>
    <span class="pl-kos">(</span>$e<span class="pl-kos">:</span>expr =&gt; $i<span class="pl-kos">:</span>item<span class="pl-kos">)</span> =&gt; <span class="pl-kos">{</span>
        #<span class="pl-kos">[</span>doc = $e<span class="pl-kos">]</span>
        $i
    <span class="pl-kos">}</span><span class="pl-kos">;</span>
<span class="pl-kos">}</span>

<span class="pl-en">forward_inner_docs</span><span class="pl-en">!</span><span class="pl-kos">(</span>include_str!<span class="pl-kos">(</span><span class="pl-s">"lib.rs"</span><span class="pl-kos">)</span> =&gt; <span class="pl-k">struct</span> <span class="pl-v">S</span> <span class="pl-kos">{</span><span class="pl-kos">}</span><span class="pl-kos">)</span><span class="pl-kos">;</span></pre></div>
<p dir="auto">The other is to use <code class="notranslate">doc(include)</code>:</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-rust notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=" #![feature(external_doc)]
 #[doc(include = &quot;lib.rs&quot;)]
 struct S {}"><pre class="notranslate"> <span class="pl-c1">#!<span class="pl-kos">[</span>feature<span class="pl-kos">(</span>external_doc<span class="pl-kos">)</span><span class="pl-kos">]</span></span>
 <span class="pl-c1">#<span class="pl-kos">[</span>doc<span class="pl-kos">(</span>include = <span class="pl-s">"lib.rs"</span><span class="pl-kos">)</span><span class="pl-kos">]</span></span>
 <span class="pl-k">struct</span> <span class="pl-smi">S</span> <span class="pl-kos">{</span><span class="pl-kos">}</span></pre></div>
<p dir="auto">The first works, but is non-trivial for people to discover, and<br>
difficult to read and maintain. The second is a strange special-case for<br>
a particular use of the macro. This generalizes it to work for any use<br>
case, not just including files.</p>
<p dir="auto">I plan to remove <code class="notranslate">doc(include)</code> when this is stabilized<br>
(<a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="816940886" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/82539" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/82539/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/82539">#82539</a>). The <code class="notranslate">forward_inner_docs</code><br>
workaround will still compile without warnings, but I expect it to be<br>
used less once it's no longer necessary.</p>
    </div>
  </task-lists>
  
</div>

      </div>

