    <tr class="d-block">
      <td class="d-block comment-body markdown-body  js-comment-body">
          <blockquote>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Expanding <code class="notranslate">mac!()</code> in a way making its result visible to <code class="notranslate">macro_attr2</code> should be somewhat annoying from the implementation point of view (I didn't investigate details).</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p dir="auto">Do you mean <code class="notranslate">macro_attr1</code> or do attribute macros evaluate from the outermost to the innermost? I would have assumed <code class="notranslate">macro_attr1</code> would be applied on the result of <code class="notranslate">doc</code>; <code class="notranslate">doc</code> on the result of <code class="notranslate">macro_attr</code>; and <code class="notranslate">macro_attr2</code> on the result of <code class="notranslate">derive</code>.</p>

      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
</task-lists>


