    <div class="Details-content--hidden mt-2">
      <pre class="color-fg-muted ws-pre-wrap">Store skeletons in $OUT_DIR as opposed to .output, which is kind of the
proper thing to do (though it certainly doesn't help
discoverability...) and it is more in line with how examples in
libbpf-rs work. Also remove the "there is hope!" comments, because even
with <a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="837337020" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/83366" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/rust-lang/rust/pull/83366/hovercard" href="https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/83366">rust-lang/rust#83366</a> resolved we still
cannot use the concat! macro in #[path = ...] attributes. All hope is
lost.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Müller &lt;deso@posteo.net&gt;</pre>
    </div>
